Here's a simple HTML web app that starts with one emoji and makes them "explode" by doubling the amount every second. This example uses embedded CSS and JavaScript to achieve the effect. You can copy and paste this code into an HTML file and open it in your browser to see it in action.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Emoji Explosion</title>
    <style>
        body {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            background-color: #282c34;
            margin: 0;
            font-size: 2rem;
            color: white;
        }
        .emoji {
            transition: transform 0.5s; 
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div id="emoji-container"></div>

<script>
    const emojis = ['ðŸŽ‰', 'ðŸ’¥', 'ðŸŒŸ', 'ðŸš€', 'ðŸ”¥', 'ðŸ€', 'ðŸŽˆ', 'ðŸŒˆ', 'âœ¨', 'ðŸŒ»'];
    const container = document.getElementById("emoji-container");

    function getRandomEmoji() {
        return emojis[Math.floor(Math.random() * emojis.length)];
    }

    function explodeEmojis() {
        let currentCount = 1;

        // Add the initial emoji
        container.innerHTML += getRandomEmoji();

        const interval = setInterval(() => {
            // Double the emojis on every tick
            currentCount *= 2;
            container.innerHTML += getRandomEmoji().repeat(currentCount);

            // If the number of emojis exceeds a certain amount, clear the interval
            if (currentCount > 1024) { 
                clearInterval(interval);
                container.innerHTML = ""; // Clear after explosion
            }
        }, 1000);
    }

    explodeEmojis();
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:
- The app starts with an initial emoji and uses an interval to double the number of emojis displayed every second.
- A random emoji is selected from a predefined array of emojis (`emojis`).
- The `explodeEmojis` function manages the emoji explosion and keeps adding new emojis until it reaches a limit (in this case, when the count exceeds 1024, it clears them).
- CSS is used to style the body and the emojis.

To test it, save the code above into an `.html` file and open it in any web browser. Enjoy the emoji explosion!

