### Explanation:
- The app initializes one emoji and sets an interval that runs every second.
- For each interval, it calculates the current count of emojis to be added, doubling the count each time.
- The new emojis are continuously appended to the container without ever clearing the previous ones, allowing for an infinite explosion effect.
- CSS is used to style the display, ensuring the emojis appear in a flexible, adaptable layout.

To try this out, save the above code in an HTML file and open it in any web browser. You should see an infinite explosion of emojis!
